INT. RAIN-SOAKED STATION - NIGHT

The last train has gone. MARA, 17, holds a cracked red umbrella beneath the platform clock. The clock reads 23:47.

Across the tracks, an empty train arrives without headlights. Its doors open, but nobody steps out.

MARA
You are three years late.

The station announcement crackles, repeating Mara's name backward. She closes the umbrella and steps toward the yellow line.

EXT. STATION FOOTBRIDGE - CONTINUOUS

Mara sees a child-sized silhouette inside the dark carriage. The red umbrella is now open on the empty platform below.
